&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;EVG Specialty Network is seeking a highly organized, detail-oriented&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative &amp;amp; Logistics Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt; to support key initiatives across Talent Acquisition, Marketing, and Operations while providing on-site administrative support at Friendship Hospital for Animals in NW Washington, DC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;This is a dynamic, hands-on role ideal for someone who thrives on keeping projects moving, managing logistics, coordinating events, and ensuring exceptional experiences for candidates, employees, and hospital leadership. You&#39;ll play a critical role in improving operational efficiency across our growing network while supporting meaningful work that advances veterinary medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Recruiting Events &amp;amp; Conference Logistics&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate logistics for conferences, career fairs, recruiting events, and industry meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare, pack, ship, track, and manage event materials and collateral&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain inventory of recruiting supplies and promotional items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage pre- and post-event logistics, including shipping, returns, and storage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide backup support for urgent or last-minute shipment needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with post-event outreach and lead management activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Marketing Collateral &amp;amp; Inventory Management&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee inventory of recruiting and marketing materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate ordering, storage, and distribution of branded collateral and promotional products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing to ensure materials remain current, on-brand, and aligned with company standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Candidate Experience &amp;amp; New Hire Gifting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate travel, scheduling, and on-site visit logistics for candidates as part of our white-glove recruiting experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage travel arrangements and reimbursement processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate welcome gifts and onboarding materials for veterinarians, hospital leaders, and home office team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee ordering, packaging, and delivery of recognition and welcome gifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Employee Recognition &amp;amp; Engagement&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track employee milestones, certifications, anniversaries, and achievements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate recognition gifts, cards, and communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing to support internal and external recognition initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Cross-Functional Operations Support&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Talent Acquisition, Marketing, Operations, and hospital leadership teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support operational compliance requirements, facility licensing, and regulatory submissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside the Chief of Staff to prioritize projects and manage competing priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure continuity and coverage for critical logistics functions across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;On-Site Housing Management&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate housing reservations and scheduling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage cleaning services, supply restocking, and maintenance requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with facilities and leadership teams to ensure accommodations remain guest-ready&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Administrative Support for Hospital Leadership&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Our Team as a Primary Care Veterinarian at Coral Springs Animal Hospital!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Are you ready to join an elite network of pathfinders paving the way for a new era of veterinary medicine? Are you ready to collaborate, innovate and elevate standards of care in the veterinary industry?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coral Springs Animal Hospital&lt;/strong&gt; is excited to announce we are expanding our &lt;strong&gt;Primary Care&lt;/strong&gt; services and are seeking skilled veterinarians to join our well-established team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Care:&lt;/strong&gt; We provide General Practice, Emergency, and Specialty care with a dedicated team of specialists in Internal Medicine, Surgery, Oncology, Emergency, and Sports Medicine &amp;amp; Rehabilitation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cutting-Edge Technology:&lt;/strong&gt; Our AAHA-accredited hospital is equipped with advanced diagnostic and treatment tools, including digital radiography, ultrasound, endoscopy, CT capabilities, fluoroscopy, laparoscopy, and hyperbaric oxygen therapy.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incredible Work Environment:&lt;/strong&gt; Be part of a community of specialists advancing veterinary medicine. Dive into a transformative culture that pushes the boundaries of veterinary care while making a meaningful impact on the lives of pets and their families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mentorship and Growth:&lt;/strong&gt; Benefit from personalized mentorship programs and career advancement opportunities. We support your professional development, providing an environment for growth, regardless of your career goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Located in South Florida, Coral Springs offers sunny weather year-round and a wide variety of outdoor activities, beautiful beaches, nature, shopping, dining, and a vibrant arts and culture scene. It’s one of the most sought-after suburban areas, balancing quiet, charming neighborhoods with exciting destinations, events, and activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You’ll provide compassionate and comprehensive care to our small animal patients and their families via diagnostic, therapeutic, and routine surgical services. You’ll also collaborate with a team of other primary care veterinarians, board certified specialists, and experienced support staff for continuity of care. You&#39;ll support internal referral growth within the hospital and contribute to building the General Practice service through community outreach and referring veterinarian engagement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Need&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Our ideal candidate&amp;nbsp;enjoys building long-term client relationships while practicing high-quality medicine in a collaborative environmen

&lt;p&gt;Friendship Hospital for Animals (FHA) is a large, full-service veterinary hospital providing specialty, emergency, and primary care for pets. Our team includes board-certified specialists in surgery, internal medicine, oncology, neurology, cardiology, dermatology, and more. Alongside these specialty services, our hospital is committed to providing high-quality primary and integrative care — combining traditional veterinary medicine with complementary therapies when appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are hiring a full-time Integrative Veterinary Medicine Doctor to provide compassionate, holistic care for our general and integrative patients. You will deliver routine wellness and preventive care while also offering integrative modalities — nutrition, rehab, acupuncture, and more — for patients and families seeking a whole-pet approach. We prioritize a joint approach to patient care, collaborating heavily with our primary care and rehabilitation teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Examine, diagnose, and treat pets for routine wellness care, illness, and injury.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage individualized treatment plans combining conventional medicine and integrative therapies (nutrition, physical rehab, acupuncture, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine procedures (vaccinations, wellness visits, diagnostics, follow-ups) and integrative follow-up care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with specialists and hospital staff to coordinate care when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide client education on preventive health, nutrition, lifestyle, and wellness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear, compassionate, and timely client communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document all patient interactions and treatments thoroughly in medical records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Environment:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Work alongside a team of experienced veterinary specialists and support staff dedicated to providing the highest quality of care. Our collaborative approach ensures comprehensive treatment plans tailored to each patient’s needs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work with Rotating Interns:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;At Friendship Hospital for Animals, you will have the opportunity to mentor and collaborate with our small animal rotating interns. This program allows for a dynamic exchange of knowledge and expertise, fostering a rich learning environment for both interns and seasoned professionals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Living in the DC Area:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Located in the vibrant Washington, DC area, our hospital offers the perfect blend of professional opportunity and quality of life. Enjoy world-class cultural attractions, diverse dining options, beautiful parks, and a dynamic community. The DC area provides excellent educational institutions and a wide range of recreational activities, making it an ideal place for families and individuals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commitment to Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;At Friendship Hospital for Animals, we prioritize continuous learning and professional development. We support our team members with ongoing education and training opportunities to stay at the forefront of veterinary oncology.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;State-of-the-Art Facilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Our hospital is equipped with the latest technology and modern amenities, providing a comfortable and efficient workspace for our team. Our ongoing commitment to investing in the best tools for our staff and patients ensures we maintain the highest standards of care.&lt;/p&gt;
