&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join the Veterinary Care and Specialty Group Team as we expand our services!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Veterinary Care &amp;amp; Specialty Group&lt;/strong&gt; (VCSG) in Chattanooga, TN is seeking an Urgent Care Veterinarian to help launch and grow our newly developed urgent care service. This new service marks the next step in our plan to further elevate the continuity and accessibility of advanced veterinary care in the area. This is a unique opportunity to join a respected specialty hospital at a pivotal moment of expansion and to play a key role in shaping the future of veterinary medicine at &lt;strong&gt;VCSG&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VCSG&lt;/strong&gt; is a premier regional small-animal emergency and referral hospital situated at the foot of Lookout Mountain, along the Tennessee River. We are able to provide uncompromised care to even the most challenging cases from the tri-state area and beyond through interdepartmental collaboration and our state of the art facility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Care:&lt;/strong&gt; Our mission at Veterinary Care as Specialty Group is to provide compassionate, advanced referral and emergency care.&amp;nbsp; Our Services include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-24/7 Emergency Care&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Critical Care&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Surgery-Orthopedic and Soft Tissue&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Internal Medicine&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Neurology&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Cardiology&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Medical Oncology&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Radiation Oncology&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Physical Rehabilitation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent Location- &lt;/strong&gt;Chattanooga, nestled in the picturesque Appalachian Mountains and bordered by the Tennessee River, offers a unique blend of natural beauty and urban amenities. Known as the “Scenic City,” Chattanooga is a haven for outdoor enthusiasts with activities like hiking, kayaking, and biking readily available. The city boasts a thriving arts and culture scene, with attractions such as the Hunter Museum of American Art and the Tivoli Theatre. &amp;nbsp;The city also offers a variety of dining, shopping, and entertainment options, making it a vibrant place to live and work.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;State of the Art Facility&lt;/strong&gt; with &lt;strong&gt;Cutting Edge Technology&lt;/strong&gt; - including ultrasound, digital radiology, CT scanning, and advanced laboratory resources. Our main ER hospital is equipped with an in-house 1.5 Tesla MRI, 128-slice CT scanner, C-arm, high-flow oxygen ventilation, long-term ventilator, and onsite blood bank to ensure the highest standard of patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; Cancer Center&lt;/strong&gt; serves as a central hub for various departments within our facility, encompassing critical areas like medical and radiation oncology. It is home to our new Varian 2024 Edge Linear Accelerator, representing a significant leap in our treatment capabilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Environment-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Work alongside a people-oriented team that cares for each other and likes to have fun at work! Our collaborative approach ensures comprehensive treatment plans tailored to each patient’s needs. &amp;nbsp;Learning and development are paramount, as we have a rotating internship program and a residency program in surgery. We are committed to fostering mentorship, promoting continuing education, and providing ample career growth opportunities for our team members.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Perks-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
